	     Johannesburg – A six-month-old baby boy died on Wednesday morning after a dog bit him several times at his home in Primrose, Johannesburg, paramedics said.  When the paramedics arrived at the scene, the body of the toddler was found in the living room of the house, ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said in a statement.  "Unfortunately, the boy had already succumbed to his injuries. Nothing more could be done and he was declared dead," he added. Meiring said the exact circumstances surrounding the incident was unknown.  Authorities were on the scene for further investigation.  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  